                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" hclass="sense" id="amniocentesis_sng_1" htag="li"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">a medical test that involves taking some liquid from a pregnant woman’s <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/womb" title="womb definition"><span class="ndv">womb</span></a> in order to find out if the baby has particular illnesses or health problems</span></span><ul class="examples" hclass="examples" htag="ul"><li class="" htag="li"><span class="x">Pregnant women over the age of 35 will be offered (an) amniocentesis.</span></li></ul><div class="collapse" hclass="collapse" htag="div"><span class="unbox" unbox="wordorigin" id="amniocentesis_unbox_1"><span class="box_title">Word Origin</span><span class="body"><span class="p">1950s: from <span class="ei">amnion</span>(mid 17th cent.: from Greek, ‘caul’, diminutive of <span class="ei">amnos</span> ‘lamb’) + Greek <span class="ei">kentēsis</span> ‘pricking’ (from <span class="ei">kentein</span> ‘to prick’).</span></span></span></div>    <div id="ring-links-box">
